      • getDefaultValueMetaData

        public java.lang.String getDefaultValueMetaData()
        Get default value meta data For all types : if _value not null, return it. For Ip Address : ip address can only be set during deployment. It can from user input or default value. if it has default value, then return it. Otherwise, it must be set by user. For String : if no default value defined in metadata case 1: minLen is null or 0, return "" case 2: minLen > 0, its value should have been set during deployment For URL & Email & License & Hostname & Iplist : same as String For UNIT64 & UINT32 & PERCENT : if no default, set to 0
        Returns:
        default value string. Null when no default values needed.
